<HEADLINE> Woman May Have Mistreated 75 Dogs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VACAVILLE, Calif. (AP) -- A woman arrested after authorities  
discovered 75 poodles wading through 6 inches of feces in her home 
said the dogs were her whole life and she didn't mean them any 
harm. 
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't mean for it to go this far,'' said Nancy Jean  
O'Neill, 48. 
</P>
<P>
	Police responded after neighbors complained about the stench  
coming from O'Neill's condo. Authorities said one dog was dead when 
they arrived Wednesday and others were in poor condition. 
</P>
<P>
	The condo was ruled uninhabitable after firefighters had to use  
breathing equipment to counter the overpowering odor. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators found sales receipts from 1986, police Lt. Ed  
Goldberg said. ``There are indications of it being a puppy mill,'' 
he said. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Neill, who was jailed, said she only wanted to keep the  
animals out of the pound and she kept them fed and watered. They 
were taken in by Humane Animal Services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
