<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-26 16:12:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mo. Town Reeling after Girl's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PACIFIC, Mo. (AP) -- The police account is the stuff of  
nightmares: a 3-year-old girl left to die in a field on a winter 
day, her mother passed out drunk at home. 
</P>
<P>
	Police are calling it a homicide and have two suspects in  
custody: an 8-year-old girl and a 6-year-old boy. 
</P>
<P>
	Police Chief Ronald Reed would not provide any more details or  
say Friday whether the two children would face charges. There are 
no other suspects, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The story began in this small community a half-hour west of St.  
Louis on the afternoon of Feb. 19, when Butch Horner returned home 
from work. According to Reed, Horner found Billie Karns, 42, the 
mother of his daughter, passed out drunk on the kitchen table. 
</P>
<P>
	But their daughter, Ciara Horner, couldn't be found.  
</P>
<P>
	Horner flagged down officers and after an hour's search, Ciara  
was found naked and unconscious in a soggy field near a drainage 
ditch, about a quarter-mile from her home. Her clothes were found 
nearby. She died a short time later of hypothermia. The temperature 
was in the 40s that day. 
</P>
<P>
	There was no evidence she had been sexually assaulted. Reed said  
interviews and other physical evidence led him to conclude that the 
two neighborhood children were responsible for Ciara's death. 
</P>
<P>
	Jody Hicks, whose husband runs a resale shop across the street  
from the trailer park where Ciara lived, smiled as she recalled the 
quiet little mop-haired blonde in Teletubbies sneakers. 
</P>
<P>
	``Shy little girl -- a little bitty thing. Cute as a bug,'' she  
said, her smile turning to a gentle sob. 
</P>
<P>
	Horner has moved out of the trailer and couldn't be reached  
Friday. But on Thursday, he said the children should not be blamed 
for Ciara's death. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know who they are, and I don't want to know,'' he told  
the St. Louis Post-Dispatch. ``I'm sure whatever happened was an 
accident. I'm sure those young kids couldn't have wanted to hurt 
Ciara.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Karns was arrested on suspicion of child endangerment. She is  
being held in jail on $2,500 bond. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
