<HEADLINE> Man Pleads Guilty to HIV Exposure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MAYVILLE, N.Y. (AP) -- A 21-year-old man pleaded guilty Friday to  
statutory rape and exposing women to the AIDS virus. 
</P>
<P>
	Nushawn Williams faces a prison term of four to 12 years on the  
Chautauqua County charges. Authorities believe he exposed more than 
a dozen young women to the virus. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams was convicted earlier this month in New York City for  
exposing a 15-year-old girl to the virus. He is already serving a 
one-to-three-year sentence for selling crack and could receive an 
additional two to seven years for the conviction. 
</P>
<P>
	In October 1997, the case caused health officials to take the  
extraordinary step of identifying Williams publicly, in the name of 
public safety. 
</P>
<P>
	State Health Department officials said a sweeping HIV-reporting  
and partner notification program is expected to begin in the spring 
in response to the Williams case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
