<HEADLINE>  Students Storm Lebanese Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARNOUN, Lebanon (AP) -- About 2,000 college students shouting  
``Death to Israel'' broke the Israeli military cordon around a 
southern Lebanese village today, cutting through barbed wire and 
crossing a declared minefield. 
</P>
<P>
	The students, Christians and Muslims from universities around  
Lebanon, were angered at Israel's takeover last week of Arnoun, 
three miles north of the Israeli border. 
</P>
<P>
	``Let the whole world know that Arnoun is Lebanese, the whole  
