<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rangers' Gretzky Out Up to a Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Wayne Gretzky, who has complained of neck pain  
for most of the season and recently of numbness and weakness in an 
arm, will be sidelined for two to four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	``Gretzky is suffering from a disc protrusion in his cervical  
spine,'' New York Rangers general manager Neil Smith said before 
Friday night's game against Phoenix. ``It is not a serious disc 
problem. Surgery is not even an issue at this time.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The NHL's career scoring leader, who had played in 223  
consecutive games, was told Friday by Dr. Patrick O'Leary to rest 
for 10 days and take anti-inflammatory medicine. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hopefully I'll be up and skating in a few weeks,'' Gretzky  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Gretzky said the injury was probably an accumulation of all the  
hits he had taken during the season. 
</P>
<P>
	``Now I've had two back injuries (in the last seven years) and I  
have proof that I have been hit over the years,'' said Gretzky, 
disputing the myth that he is never hit hard on the ice. 
</P>
<P>
	Gretzky had a serious back injury that kept him out during most  
of the 1992-93 season. He had not missed a game since signing with 
the Rangers as a free agent in the summer of 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	He first complained about neck pains last month after a game in  
Washington and was later knocked to the ice against Carolina and 
complained about his back. 
</P>
<P>
	``I thought I had a stiff neck,'' Gretzky said, ``and we just  
treated it with heat.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He said the condition worsened when the Rangers went on a  
two-game road trip to Edmonton and Calgary this week. Gretzky said 
he had to turn his body completely around to look to his right. He 
said there was also some numbness in one of his arms. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury ``definitely peaked in Edmonton and Calgary, but I  
was not going to'' sit out, said Gretzky, who had spent the early 
part of his career with the Oilers. 
</P>
<P>
	On Wednesday, he missed practice, saying he was unable to grip  
his stick because of pain in his arms. He underwent an MRI on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	For the third straight year, Gretzky led the Rangers in scoring.  
After 58 games this season, Gretzky had eight goals and 49 assists 
for 57 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Gretzky said he was sorry to see his consecutive-games streak  
end, but was more concerned with getting himself ready to play 
again. 
</P>
<P>
	``I just have to follow what I've been told,'' he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
