<HEADLINE> Sch,0134  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NAPLES, Fla. (AP) -- Arnold Palmer is cutting back his Senior PGA  
Tour schedule. 
</P>
<P>
	``I played last week, I'm playing this week ... and that could  
be it probably for a long time,'' Palmer said Thursday as he 
prepared for today's opening round in the ACE Group Classic. ``If 
my golf game continues to be as poor as it is, I won't play at 
all.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Palmer, who will turn 70 in September, said he has fully  
recovered from prostate cancer and has no other serious ailments. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm playing in Naples because my sister lives here and I'm  
doing a golf course here,'' he said. ``But I'm not happy with my 
game. My iron play is atrocious and it has not been good for a long 
time.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
