<HEADLINE> Maple Leafs' McAllister Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Chris McAllister, a defenseman with Toronto, was  
suspended for two games without pay for leaving the bench and 
becoming involved in a fight, the NHL said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	McAllister left the bench during the second period of Thursday  
night's game against the New York Islanders, then was assessed a 
major penalty for fighting and a game misconduct. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is unacceptable for any player to leave the players' bench  
even on a legal line change for the purpose of either initiating or 
becoming involved in an altercation,'' NHL director of operations 
Colin Campbell said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	McAllister will lose $3,489.58, which the NHL said would go to  
the league's Emergency Assistance Fund. 
