<HEADLINE> Dolphins Sign Willie Green </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAVIE, Fla. (AP) -- Wide receiver Willie Green, owner of two  
Super Bowl rings as Denver's third wide receiver, has signed a 
three-year contract with the Miami Dolphins. 
</P>
<P>
	Financial terms were not disclosed. The sides initially were  
discussing an incentive-laden deal worth up to $3 million. 
</P>
<P>
	``If I could not have gotten on a team with playoff potential, I  
would have walked away from football,'' Green said. ``I could have 
done that with no remorse or regret. This isn't about money. It's 
about me having a chance to win a third consecutive Super Bowl.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Green, who turns 33 in April, caught just 16 passes for 194  
yards and one touchdown last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining the Broncos, Green was a two-year starter as one  
of the original Carolina Panthers. He caught 47 passes for 882 
yards and six TDs in 1995, following that with 46 catches in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	Green began his career with Detroit and spent one year in Tampa  
Bay before going to the Panthers. 
